Nollywood actress, Omotola Jalade-Ekeinde, has revealed that she tested positive to the deadly coronavirus disease. The actress, who disclosed this via her Instagram account on Saturday evening, said she’s been ill and in isolation but she’s currently getting better. She also expressed how sad she felt about the death of the Nigerian youths being crushed daily by trailers or containers on the road. She said” Hello all, I know most of you have been wondering where I have been. “Well, I contracted COVID-19, I have been ill in Isolation and now getting better. “I will be releasing more details on this soon. ”However, I have been reading devastating news on how our youths die every by getting crushed by trailers or containers. “This is disheartening and has made my heart really troubled. “This can happen to anyone and enforcements shouldn’t be taken lightly on this. “I will call on the Lagos Government to please do something about it. “Thanks for your love and care as I recover fully.” See picture below… <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-829274" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/IMG_3449.jpg" alt="" width="1242" height="590" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/IMG_3449.jpg 1242w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/IMG_3449-300x143.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/IMG_3449-1024x486.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1242px) 100vw, 1242px">